   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Customer Segmentation Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Project Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook analyzes customer behavior data to segment customers using descriptive statistics and exploratory clustering-style analysis. We focus on spend patterns, recency, frequency, and engagement to create actionable customer groups.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Build RFM (Recency, Frequency, Monetary) analysis from transaction data.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Segment customers into meaningful groups using quantile-based methods.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Profile each segment with descriptive statistics and visualizations.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Translate segments into actionable marketing strategies.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Business / Research Problem\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Treating all customers the same wastes marketing budget and misses retention opportunities. Segmentation enables targeted messaging, personalized offers, and better resource allocation.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Why This Analysis Matters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"RFM segmentation is one of the most practical and widely-used customer analytics techniques. It requires only transaction data and produces immediately actionable segments.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetic dataset of **8,000 transactions** from **1,500 customers** over 12 months with: `customer_id`, `transaction_date`, `amount`, `product_category`, `channel`.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetically generated for educational purposes.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Environment Setup\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\", \\\"numpy\\\", \\\"matplotlib\\\", \\\"seaborn\\\", \\\"scipy\\\"]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    except ImportError:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, \\\"-m\\\", \\\"pip\\\", \\\"install\\\", \\\"-q\\\", pkg])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m004\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Imports\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import numpy as np\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import seaborn as sns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from scipy import stats\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import warnings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.set_style(\\\"whitegrid\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"%matplotlib inline\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m005\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Configuration / Constants\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"SEED = 42\\n\",\n",
    "    \"N_CUSTOMERS = 1500\\n\",\n",
    "    \"N_TRANSACTIONS = 8000\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ANALYSIS_DATE = pd.Timestamp(\\\"2026-01-01\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"CATEGORIES = [\\\"Electronics\\\", \\\"Clothing\\\", \\\"Home\\\", \\\"Food\\\", \\\"Books\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"CHANNELS = [\\\"Online\\\", \\\"In-Store\\\", \\\"Mobile App\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Configuration loaded.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m006\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Generation\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c004\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"rng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"dates = pd.date_range(\\\"2025-01-01\\\", \\\"2025-12-31\\\", freq=\\\"D\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"customer_ids = [f\\\"C{i:04d}\\\" for i in range(1, N_CUSTOMERS + 1)]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Assign customer spending profiles\\n\",\n",
    "    \"customer_profiles = {}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for cid in customer_ids:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    tier = rng.choice([\\\"high\\\", \\\"medium\\\", \\\"low\\\"], p=[0.15, 0.35, 0.50])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    customer_profiles[cid] = tier\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"rows = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i in range(N_TRANSACTIONS):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    cid = rng.choice(customer_ids)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    tier = customer_profiles[cid]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    avg_spend = {\\\"high\\\": 150, \\\"medium\\\": 60, \\\"low\\\": 25}[tier]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    amount = max(5, round(rng.normal(avg_spend, avg_spend * 0.5), 2))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    rows.append({\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"customer_id\\\": cid,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"transaction_date\\\": rng.choice(dates),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"amount\\\": amount,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"product_category\\\": rng.choice(CATEGORIES),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"channel\\\": rng.choice(CHANNELS, p=[0.45, 0.35, 0.20]),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    })\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = pd.DataFrame(rows)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"transaction_date\\\"] = pd.to_datetime(df[\\\"transaction_date\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Transactions: {len(df):,}, Unique customers: {df['customer_id'].nunique()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.head()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m007\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Data Validation Checks\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c005\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Missing values: {df.isnull().sum().sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Negative amounts: {(df['amount'] < 0).sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Date range: {df['transaction_date'].min()} → {df['transaction_date'].max()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"✅ Validation passed.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m008\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Data Cleaning\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Dataset is clean. In practice, remove test transactions, refunds, and employee purchases.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m009\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## RFM Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We compute Recency (days since last purchase), Frequency (number of transactions), and Monetary (total spend) for each customer.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c006\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"rfm = df.groupby(\\\"customer_id\\\").agg(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    recency=(\\\"transaction_date\\\", lambda x: (ANALYSIS_DATE - x.max()).days),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    frequency=(\\\"transaction_date\\\", \\\"count\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    monetary=(\\\"amount\\\", \\\"sum\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \").reset_index()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"rfm[\\\"avg_order_value\\\"] = rfm[\\\"monetary\\\"] / rfm[\\\"frequency\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"RFM table: {rfm.shape}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"rfm.describe().round(1)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m010\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Exploratory Data Analysis / Univariate Analysis\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c007\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(16, 4))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].hist(rfm[\\\"recency\\\"], bins=30, color=\\\"steelblue\\\", edgecolor=\\\"white\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"Recency (days)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].hist(rfm[\\\"frequency\\\"], bins=20, color=\\\"seagreen\\\", edgecolor=\\\"white\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"Frequency (transactions)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].hist(rfm[\\\"monetary\\\"], bins=30, color=\\\"coral\\\", edgecolor=\\\"white\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].set_title(\\\"Monetary (total spend $)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m011\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Segmentation\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We use quantile-based scoring: each RFM component gets a score of 1-4 (quartiles). For Recency, lower is better (more recent), so scoring is inverted.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c008\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"rfm[\\\"R_score\\\"] = pd.qcut(rfm[\\\"recency\\\"], 4, labels=[4, 3, 2, 1]).astype(int)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"rfm[\\\"F_score\\\"] = pd.qcut(rfm[\\\"frequency\\\"].rank(method=\\\"first\\\"), 4, labels=[1, 2, 3, 4]).astype(int)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"rfm[\\\"M_score\\\"] = pd.qcut(rfm[\\\"monetary\\\"].rank(method=\\\"first\\\"), 4, labels=[1, 2, 3, 4]).astype(int)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"rfm[\\\"RFM_score\\\"] = rfm[\\\"R_score\\\"] + rfm[\\\"F_score\\\"] + rfm[\\\"M_score\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"def assign_segment(row):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if row[\\\"RFM_score\\\"] >= 10:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        return \\\"Champions\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    elif row[\\\"RFM_score\\\"] >= 8:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        return \\\"Loyal\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    elif row[\\\"RFM_score\\\"] >= 6:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        return \\\"Potential\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    elif row[\\\"RFM_score\\\"] >= 4:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        return \\\"At Risk\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    else:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        return \\\"Lost\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"rfm[\\\"segment\\\"] = rfm.apply(assign_segment, axis=1)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(rfm[\\\"segment\\\"].value_counts())\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m012\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Bivariate / Multivariate Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Segment profiles\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c009\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"seg_profile = rfm.groupby(\\\"segment\\\").agg(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    count=(\\\"customer_id\\\", \\\"count\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    avg_recency=(\\\"recency\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    avg_frequency=(\\\"frequency\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    avg_monetary=(\\\"monetary\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    avg_aov=(\\\"avg_order_value\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \").round(1)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"seg_profile[\\\"pct\\\"] = (seg_profile[\\\"count\\\"] / seg_profile[\\\"count\\\"].sum() * 100).round(1)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"seg_profile[\\\"revenue_share\\\"] = rfm.groupby(\\\"segment\\\")[\\\"monetary\\\"].sum()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"seg_profile[\\\"revenue_share\\\"] = (seg_profile[\\\"revenue_share\\\"] / seg_profile[\\\"revenue_share\\\"].sum() * 100).round(1)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"=== Segment Profiles ===\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"seg_profile\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c010\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"seg_order = [\\\"Champions\\\", \\\"Loyal\\\", \\\"Potential\\\", \\\"At Risk\\\", \\\"Lost\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"colors = [\\\"#2ecc71\\\", \\\"#3498db\\\", \\\"#f1c40f\\\", \\\"#e67e22\\\", \\\"#e74c3c\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"seg_counts = rfm[\\\"segment\\\"].value_counts().reindex(seg_order)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].bar(seg_counts.index, seg_counts.values, color=colors)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"Customer Count by Segment\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=30)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"seg_rev = rfm.groupby(\\\"segment\\\")[\\\"monetary\\\"].sum().reindex(seg_order)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].bar(seg_rev.index, seg_rev.values, color=colors)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"Total Revenue by Segment\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=30)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c011\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 7))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for seg, color in zip(seg_order, colors):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    subset = rfm[rfm[\\\"segment\\\"] == seg]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    ax.scatter(subset[\\\"recency\\\"], subset[\\\"monetary\\\"], alpha=0.4, label=seg, color=color, s=20)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_xlabel(\\\"Recency (days)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_ylabel(\\\"Total Monetary ($)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"Customer Segments: Recency vs Monetary\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.legend()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m013\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Feature-Specific Insights\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Channel preference by segment\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c012\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"df_with_seg = df.merge(rfm[[\\\"customer_id\\\", \\\"segment\\\"]], on=\\\"customer_id\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"channel_seg = pd.crosstab(df_with_seg[\\\"segment\\\"], df_with_seg[\\\"channel\\\"], normalize=\\\"index\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"channel_seg = channel_seg.reindex(seg_order)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"channel_seg.plot(kind=\\\"bar\\\", stacked=True, figsize=(10, 5), colormap=\\\"Set2\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.title(\\\"Channel Mix by Segment\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.ylabel(\\\"Proportion\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.xticks(rotation=30)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m014\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Statistical Checks\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c013\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"groups = [group[\\\"monetary\\\"].values for _, group in rfm.groupby(\\\"segment\\\")]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"stat, p = stats.kruskal(*groups)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Kruskal-Wallis test (monetary across segments): H={stat:.2f}, p={p:.6f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Segments differ significantly: {p < 0.05}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m015\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Key Findings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Champions represent a small fraction of customers but contribute disproportionately to revenue.**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **At Risk and Lost segments have high recency values** — they haven't purchased recently and need re-engagement.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Potential customers have moderate frequency** — targeted incentives could push them toward Loyal status.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Channel preferences differ by segment,** enabling channel-specific campaigns.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **The monetary distribution is highly skewed** — a classic Pareto pattern.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m016\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Limitations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Synthetic data with simplified profiles.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No customer demographics or acquisition channel data.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Quantile-based segmentation is arbitrary at boundaries.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No time-based segment migration analysis.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m017\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Recommendations / Next Steps\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Champions:** Reward with loyalty programs and exclusive access.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Loyal:** Upsell and cross-sell higher-value products.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Potential:** Nurture with targeted email campaigns.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **At Risk:** Win-back campaigns with time-limited offers.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Lost:** Low-cost reactivation attempts; don't over-invest.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m018\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Common Mistakes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Using arbitrary RFM thresholds** without understanding the business context.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Treating segments as static.** Customers migrate between segments over time.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Ignoring the Pareto effect.** Most revenue comes from a small fraction of customers.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Over-segmenting.** Too many segments become unactionable.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Not validating segments with stakeholders.** Data-driven segments must make business sense.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m019\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Use K-Means clustering** on scaled RFM features and compare to quantile-based segments.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Add a time dimension:** track how customers move between segments over quarters.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Compute customer lifetime value** per segment.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Create a Pareto chart** showing cumulative revenue contribution.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Design a targeted campaign** for the \\\"At Risk\\\" segment with specific messaging and channel.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m020\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **RFM segmentation is practical, simple, and actionable** — a great starting point for customer analytics.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Revenue is highly concentrated in top segments** — protect and nurture Champions.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Each segment needs a different strategy** — one-size-fits-all marketing is wasteful.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Monitor segment migration over time** to measure the impact of retention programs.\"\n",
